<subSubSection id="4F9D9BCA4413FFEDFF3CFE6DFE467991" pageId="29" pageNumber="161" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0738C8414413FFEDFF3CFE6DFE467991" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFF3CFE6DFEFC7AF1" bold="true" box="[199,315,405,431]" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was described by Bernhauer (1938) from “Tcheuly-Nord: Nanye-li […]” and up to the present time it is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="D83C76E34413FFEDFDA1FE41FD077A8D" box="[602,704,441,467]" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">holotype</typeStatus>
. Measurements of the 
<typeStatus id="D83C76E34413FFEDFC38FE41FBEE7A8D" box="[963,1065,441,467]" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">holotype</typeStatus>
: HW: 1.00; HL: 0.80; OL: 0.30; TL: 0.15; 4: 0.13 × 0.05; PL: 1.10; PW: 1.30; ESL: 1.90; EW: 2.00; AW: 2.20; MTrL: 0.63 (MTrL 1–4: 0.38; MTrL 5: 0.25); BL: 5.80. In general appearance, 
<taxonomicName id="C087B3C24413FFEDFD88FDF9FCE37945" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1938" box="[627,804,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geodromicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuatocollis">
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFD88FDF9FD407945" box="[627,647,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFD6EFDF9FCE37945" box="[661,804,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">sinuatocollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C087B3C24413FFEDFC0BFDF9FAD67945" authority="(Sharp, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1008,1297,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Psephidonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuatus">
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFC0BFDF9FBC37945" box="[1008,1028,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFBE9FDFAFBA87945" box="[1042,1135,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">sinuatus</emphasis>
(Sharp, 1889)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="7F9088D14413FFEDFAAEFDF9FA5F7945" box="[1365,1432,513,539]" name="Japan" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">Japan</collectingCountry>
, from which it differs by a less convex body, larger and coarser punctation of the forebody, a scutellum without microsculpture, and by slightly shorter segments of antennae. The distinguishing characters listed above are generally variable in most species of 
<taxonomicName id="C087B3C24413FFEDFE29FD95FDAF79D9" authorityName="Redtenbacher" authorityYear="1857" box="[466,616,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geodromicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFE29FD95FDAF79D9" box="[466,616,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">Geodromicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="C087B3C24413FFEDFC96FD95FBE779D9" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1938" box="[877,1056,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geodromicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuatocollis">
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFC96FD95FC4679D9" box="[877,897,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFC6AFD95FBE779D9" box="[913,1056,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">sinuatocollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="C087B3C24413FFEDFB98FD95FB2379D9" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1123,1252,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Psephidonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuatus">
<emphasis id="35F314534413FFEDFB98FD95FB2379D9" box="[1123,1252,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">G. sinuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not proposed here because additional material (including males) from northern 
<collectingCountry id="7F9088D14413FFEDFC82FD69FC7B79F5" box="[889,956,657,683]" name="China" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">China</collectingCountry>
is required. The distribution of the species is shown in 
<figureCitation id="9FBCD4C44413FFEDFEE5FD4DFEBA7991" box="[286,381,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 113" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 113. Distribution of 21 species of Geodromicus in China: 1–G. abdominalis, 2–G. amplissimus, 3–G. aokii, 4–G. beibienkoi, 5–G. chinensis, 6–G. cupreostigma, 7–G. formosanus, 8–G. frigidus, 9–G. hammondi, 10–G. lestevoides, 11–G. magnus sp. n., 12–G. namucuoicus sp. n., 13–G. ohkurai, 14–G. philydroides, 15–G. shii sp. n., 16–G. sibiricus, 17–G. sinuatocollis, 18–G. sinuatus, 19–G. smetanai, 20–G. subquadratus sp. n., 21–G. taiwanensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884852/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="161">Fig. 113</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
